comment.text:
Heard great things about this restaurant. The hubby and I decided to take the 30min drive and try it out. Let's say it did NOT disappoint.  The food was so flavorful. Our hostesses Lis was so accommodating.  We did not have a reservation, it's highly recommended. However she was able to seat us within a small wait time. If in the area OR not and up for a drive, give them a try. You won't be disappointed.  Oh and they have FREE parking, which is rare for that area. Oh one more thing the drinks!!! Man oh man.. on point... one and done on point and I can usually have 2-3 easily lol. 

So I took a video of all the food we ordered after snapping this two? However I don't usually post here so don't know how to upload the video lol... or it could be the drink

Ambience was amazing.. it was great for late night hangout or just normal dinner and lunch
the service was impecable.. 
and the food both variation and taste is great and delicious.
it is a really good variation of indonesian foods and the mixed of flavor was amazing too

The best Indonesian food in Atlanta !

Came here for the first time with friends and we enjoyed every bites of it.
Will definitely recommend this place to friends. Too bad that I don't live in this city, otherwise will come here more often.

Service was excellent and wasn't too loud , it was nice !

comment.text:
My fiancé took me here on my birthday and I was sooo satisfied when we left. First off, the menu was so helpful if this is your first time eating Indonesian food. It was filled with soo many options to choose from plus pictures! 

Now let's get to the food! Oh my gosh it was delicious! The beef skewers had me wanting more. We also ordered the chicken skewers, crispy duck, curly corn, vegetables noodle, drinks & even dessert! And let's say there's barely any leftovers!

Everyone was sooooo nice and they even brought out a birthday ice cream for me & sang the birthday song. Definitely come back. This place deserves the hype. I don't make reviews unless I was left with an impression & this one did it for me. Give it! I'll be back.

We really enjoyed the experience, especially since we got sat in a small room in the back. The food is generally good. Many of the dishes taste a little too similar, I wonder if they are supposed to be that way. Also, the creme brulee was terrible. The texture of the cream is way off, and the sugar was not torched correctly at all... I couldn't even eat the one bite, as the cream and sugar grains were both really bad in both taste and texture...

I attended this restaurant for a friends birthday dinner. It's a cute little restaurant with a great atmosphere. Food came out pretty quickly and the drinks were pretty good. My favorite was the chicken egg pillows. They were so good that I ordered some to go as well. It is small plates and they also have some larger plates but mostly everything or small plates. So ordering one or two things is what I suggest. Prices are really reasonable as well. This would be a great lunch spot. I would go again.

***FOOD: scrumptious bite size appetiznearly everything was excellent   Had sea scallops - excellent, Soft Shel Crab Tempura- excellent, Chicken, Lamb Beef Sate were all excellent, we had 2 orders because that's how delicious they were. Fried Rice-Ok, have had better, Rijsttafel-variety of foods on a platter-overall everything was good, some items we liked more than others, we just wanted to try something different. Bali Crispy Duck - small portion and it was OK, have had better and expensive for what we got, Yellow Coconut Rice-good,  Green Crepe Roll dessert - was ok   
 


***COST (OUT OF 4$) $$ for all we got it was reasonable cost, remember these are appetizer portions $10-$12, the Rijsttafel was $30 & the Sate Tasting was $32



***DÉCOR: modern with curtains dividing dining area, booths, parking is very limited 



***SERVICE: friendly service, attentive and food came fast 



***RECOMMEND: HIGHLY RECOMMEND this place and would go back. wish they would open one up OTP

Came on a Thursday around 6 pm and was quickly seated.  Friendly staff, nice ambience, great food!

Lamb, beef, chicken sate' were delicious!! 
Rica Rica Shrimp Al Ajillo
CHICKEN & EGG PILLOWS
Pork wontons
VEGETABLE SPRINGROLLS

The  Hidden menu item: 
beef noodles were delicious!!

My favorite was also the complimentary parking in the parking deck! It's a #WIN (pun intended)

Highly recommended!

When there for my first night out postpartum. It was a new taste for me, I'm very finicky but they definitely satisfied my palate. I loved the ambiance. An the restroom was picturesque .

comment.text: Consistently delicious! Love the lamb skewer, chicken skewer, fried chicken, spring rolls, fried brussels, and corn ribs!
Stopped into WIN for a late midday bite to eat and were not disappointed. Everything we had (all small bites) were tasty and excellent. We will be back!

The typical Indonesia- India flair type of spot. The ambiance is nice and parking is great. Food is okay had better sorry. The tapas are unique rather than typical. But the seasoning was off on some of the Seafood. I would stop by for a drink at the bar but not a full meal again.

photos.caption: LS1. BALI SUNRISE FRIED RICE Nasi Goreng

comment.text: OMG this restaurant checks all the boxes, delicious food, service, kind staff, ambiance and location.  We had the lobster chicken fried rice and a bunch of small plates and Bali sauces. Our waiter was an absolute pro, cool and attentive.  Thank you!

I finally stopped by WIN to have lunch with a friend. They have some pretty great lunch specials and we decided to both do the power lunch (app and entree) for $15.

I had the Indonesian soup and the yellow curry chicken. The soup is so tasty and would be the perfect cure especially when sick. Yellow curry was delicious and the chicken had a nice smoky flavor. My friend ordered the curry fish and curly corn which she enjoyed and said was filling.

The interior is very nice. As soon as you walk in it makes an impression! They also have drink specials daily! We had the Bali 75 cocktails - so yum!

I love this place! I had been following them on Instagram for a month before I finally had time to go. After my first visit, I came back about a week later with my family and I would have been back again if I had the time lol the food is delicious, the service was great and he ambiance is very clean and cute

photos.caption: SMALL PLATES TASTING: CHICKEN & EGG PILLOWS, PATATAS BRAVAS AND CURLY CORN
LS1. BALI SUNRISE FRIED RICE Nasi Goreng

comment.text: I've had this place on my radar and it did not disappoint. The parking is kind of tricky but everything else is great, from the food, cost, drinks and service! We ordered a bunch of food and everything was delicious. My favorites were the scallops small plate and the lamb skewers. But I enjoyed everything!!

The food and atmosphere was great! Great and fast service! Drinks were so good and strong!!! I love this place and can't wait to go back and try the other things on the menu!!! 10/10 MOST DEFINITELY RECOMMEND!

Winning at WIN!! This restaurant exceeded all of my culinary expectations. If you have not been what are you really waiting for? This place is focused on Indonesian cuisine and they knock it out of the park! There are a few Indonesian spots in town and they are tasty, but this place is top notch! 

Now the location is tricky in that you could miss it and the parking garage is in the basement and the elevator may not be accessible after hours and you will have to walk outside to the deck, but who cares it's FREEE!!!

Now the decor is very very minimalist , but service is superb! There was not an unhappy diner to be found! 

If you are a fan of small and diverse plates they nail it!!!!!  The food is fresh, succulently seasoned , and perfectly executed. The price is very friendly and the cocktails are cocky baby! 

I enjoyed everything that touched my lips! My favs were the scallops, corn strips, and the soft shell crab dish.  The sambal was sooooo tasty as well as the spicy and sweet sauce accompaniments.

photos.caption: Dessert- crème brûlée - it lasted 3 seconds
SS8. PADANG SOFT SHELL CRAB TEMPURA
Lumpia veggie spring rolls - stuffed with mushrooms - Just yum!

comment.text:
Such a lovely place. Lovely staff. My friend and I came here for late night tapas one night, and we were not disappointed. First of all, I cannot believe I have been driving up and down Piedmont and I have never noticed this restaurant, but the owner let me know that they had been here for years! Anyway, I'm so glad we found it randomly on OpenTable. 
For the table, they give you a shrimp, crackers, and dipping sauce to start out with, and they offered us there a margarita of the day, which was a mango margarita, and it was five dollars. And it had a good amount of alcohol in it, which I really appreciated!
One thing I really appreciate it is that the menu has pictures! I didn't get to take a picture of it but the menu literally has a picture of every single dish and this is so important for you to set your expectations on your food and how you eat for the evening. When the food arrived, it looked exactly like the picture, and I was so happy about that. My friend and I got a variety of tapas to share. The prices are so cheap for the value received. We got this lamb satay, and we also got sides of fried rice, soft shell crab and a shrimp dish I cannot remember the name of. 
Everything was so flavorful, and different. I don't usually eat meat, and today I stepped out of my zone and had a lamb sauté, which I did not regret. It was juicy, tangy, and a little bit sweet and spicy. So so good. It's one of their most popular dishes. , which I really appreciate it. We also got visited by the general manager, and he gave us some of his suggestions on where to order and we did order some of those. We just had a lovely experience. 
I can't wait to come back here again, I've already told several friends about it. 10/10 experience

photos.caption: SS8. PADANG SOFT SHELL CRAB TEMPURA

comment.text:
Win was really good & an excellent choice for dinner last night. My friend and I wanted to try several items so instead of getting a large entree we opted for several tapas aka small plates. While we were deciding on our selections I decided to order the iced lychee tea to drink. It was really good and not overly sweet. The server also brought us complementary shrimp chips with sweet & soir dipping sauce. The chip alone didn't have much flavor but paired with the sauce they were really good. For my tapas I ordered the corn fritters, crispy brussel sprouts, and the seafood skewers.

Food:
Corn fritters- really good
Crispy brussels- I didn't realize they were going to have batter on them. I took most of the batter off & just ate the brussel. The flavor was good & paired well with the dipping sauce.
Seafood Skewers- You get6 skewers for $12. They were really tasty and made with minced swordfish and shrimp. 

Ambiance: 
 The ambiance was really nice. I loved the greenery in the bar area. I will definitely be returning to try some other items.

Thoroughly enjoyed my visit to Win last night! Service was great the moment we walked in the door and our server was attentive throughout the visit. She offered great recommendations! There were a lot of menu options and I'm glad the menu had pictures lol.
The cocktails were strong and everything we ate was delicious! My favorite was the Lamb Saté! A must try.

photos.caption: Chicken & Egg Pillows  Pandang Soft Shell Crab Tempura  Lamb Satè & Chicken Satè

comment.text: Stopped in for a mid day lunch. The service was excellent the server was attentive but the star was the food. The spring rolls were good however the lamb was amazing full of flavor I would go back for that alone. The Beef rice plate was also delicious.

So I will say my food was good. The lamb sate was lukewarm but flavor was really good. I also ordered the red snapper or flying fish and it was good but the fried rice was bland. Nothing to rave about regarding the dish, but my husband's fried noodles were delicious! However, my 3 stars comes from the service. He was actually HORRIBLE. Very nice but it took 45 minutes to get our drink and we put the drink order in with the food. By the time the drinks finally came we were done eating. We essentially had our drinks for dinner. But then the server was nowhere to be found. Mind you he had 3 tables including us. Yeah he needs to be retrained asap or they need some more staff. Just pack your patience if you come here on the weekend even with a reservation like we did.

According to the menu, WIN stands for Wonderful Indonesia. But the General Manager told me it actually stands for Wonderful Indonesian Netherlands.

Today was my second visit after being lucky enough to score a complimentary meal with some Instagram Influencer friends earlier this month. I was so absolutely impressed with the food and service that I knew beyond a shadow of a doubt I wanted this to be my next date night out with my beautiful bride. Feeding her good food is the key to a long-lasting marriage... so we jumped in the car on a Monday evening (for no particular reason) and headed down for a wonderful experience in Dutch-Indonesian cuisine.

    [ THE EXPERIENCE ]

FIRST, let me say the staff is incredibly accommodating. It seems that everyone from the server (Stephanie R) and kitchen staff to the general manager himself sees to it you are being looked after as if you are honored guests. They not only paid special attention to me and my dining companions on both my visits, but every other table was equally cared for in the same welcoming fashion. Even if the food had been mediocre (which it wasn't), I would come back simply to experience that level of care. Parking is limited in the front, but there is a free garage on the lower level just behind the restaurant which was a lovely surprise considering free is not normally in the description when parking in Atlanta proper.

The restaurant itself is nicely decorated with an upscaled casual feel. Not so upscaled that you would feel underdressed, but not so casual that nicer attire isn't warranted. Most of the tables feel more intimate towards the rear while the front gets a lot more natural light from the large glass windows. It was here I met yet another popular Instagram Influencer, enjoying her meal and doing her thang with a camera. 

     [ THE FOOD ]

On my first visit we were treated to a large assortment of menu items which included 3 different RAMENS (shrimp & tofu was my favorite), 3 different SATÉS (all delicious), Bali grilled pork BABY BACK RIBS, crispy whole RED SNAPPER, BALI CRISPY DUCK and practically every appetizer on the menu. Simply put, you can't go wrong here with any of the apps, but I wasn't a huge fan of the Red Snapper or Crispy Duck. Good, but not as flavorful as many of the other items.

On my second visit with my wife, we enjoyed the three appetizer sampler for $20. We chose:
SP6 - BRUSSELS SPROUT TEMPURA (4.5 stars)
SP2 - CRISPY CORN FRITTERS (4 stars)
SP1 - VEGGIE EGG ROLLS  (3.75 stars)

My wife decided to get out of her comfort zone and try the PLANT-BASED RENDANG (4.5 stars) while I opted for the real thing, their world-famous BEEF RENDANG (5+ stars). Both entrées cost $14 and came with pickled vegetables, coconut soup and sautéed potatoes. The plant-based rendang is made with jackfruit, but looked so much like meat that my wife had difficultly wanting to bite it. However, once she did, it passed her taste & texture gage-reflex meter despite really looking AND shredding like meat. My Beef Rendang was soooo tender and absolutely delicious that I ate a little too fast, which left me wanting more!

     [ FINAL THOUGHTS ]

We hadn't departed from the restaurant more than 5 minutes before my wife was posting on Facebook recommending WIN to some of her friends, which made me very happy. I truly HOPED she would enjoy it because she can be rather finicky with new things. After all, Bali cuisine is not in our typical restaurant rotation of flavors. We live quite a distance away, but plan on returning with even more friends as soon as possible. Everyone in our circle needs to experience what wonderful Indonesia really means! I hope those reading this review will come and have as equally a satisfying experience as we did... ENJOY!!!

2022 / 114

I've been wanting to try WIN since moving just down the street from this place. Flavors are on point and won't disappoint your tastebuds. And the price tag is nice on your wallet. 

We went on a Monday night and they had a decent crowd, a few larger parties and definitely short handed on service. But...the service we did receive was very good.  I ordered the Bali sunset and it was good and very strong.  We ordered the three meat option, pork, lamb and chicken. The lamb was by far my favorite and then the beef. The sauces are really good and the fried rice isn't one like you think. It's really very simple, yet very good with the sauces. Our bill was $65 for all this food and two drinks. This is definitely a repeat for us and one you should try. The portions are smaller but really fills you up. And don't let the simple decorations or the wait deter you from eating here. Visited on a Saturday night with my fiancé for date night. He made reservations via their website for 8:30pm and specified date night as the occasion. When we were seated we had our own little semi private area separated by curtains and it was a very cozy. 
The menu is extensive and we decided to order a few different appetizers to share. We ordered the Small Plates Tasting with vegetable spring rolls, curly corn,  land brussel sprouts tempura. We also ordered rica rica shrimp. Along with water we each ordered a Bali sunset, but I got mine with tequila instead of vodka. 
We were brought shrimp cakes which looked like rice cakes. Our drinks came shortly after. Along with looking pretty they tasted delicious. You could taste the liquor, but it was subtle not overpowering. 
The shrimp cakes were ok. They didn't have much flavor but they had a light flavor at the same time. 
The food was brought out and the plating presentation was beautiful. We couldn't wait to dig in. Other than the brussel sprout tempura having a bit too much batter, everything was delicious and they each had their own dipping sauce. The curly corn had great flavor. The spring rolls were crispy. The shrimp was tasty with a slight spice to it. 
He still wanted something else so he ordered the gohu tuna carpaccio which came out pretty quickly with beautiful presentation. This was also delicious and probably my favorite thing that we had. 
Overall it was a great experience and definitely recommend giving them a try.

photos.caption: Vegetable spring rolls, curly corn, and brussel sprout tempura

comment.text:
This is kind of a late review but it had to be written anyway because I love this place. This trip came about because of a canceled trip to Bali but our desire to still try Indonesian food. 

When you walk in, the decor is so inviting and makes you feel like you stepped into a different country. It's a mix of a lot of greenery and Indonesian art and design. We were originally sat in the back area next to a family. I appreciated the server discreetly asking if we'd like another table because the baby with the family started screaming. 

After we moved we looked over the menu and wanted to try everything so we ordered a bunch of food. There was nothing I didn't like...that's it. Okay, I didn't eat as much of the corn fritters but that's only because it was a little heavier than I wanted at the time. Everything was perfectly executed and felt like they thought of every detail to make the bite visually appealing and tasty. And a bonus is you can eat so many things at a tapas restaurant and leave with a decent bill.

I can't wait to go back.

What a cute spot!!! I've never had this food before but I love that you can get sample plates to try a little bit of everything. The service was amazing! Size of portion was perfect and the ambiance was perfect!

photos.caption: Mangarita was the special for the day

comment.text: This place was a 10/10 all across the board. All of the flavors were on point. To start off, I had the pita bread that was served with some sweet tomato sauce, amazing. I also had the chicken satè for an appetizer and my girlfriend had the shrimp small plate, both were delicious. For our entrees I had the beef rendang large plate and my girlfriend had the shrimp fried noodles. Everything was delicious! I have no complaints besides wanting more. I'll definitely be back!

comment.text: Great Service. Lovely food and peaceful . Will come back again. 5 stars. Easy parking

comment.text: Ahh I felt peace eating this entire dish. Everything just kept getting better and better. The beef was soo tender and the crepes was the best way to end my day.

photos.caption: Crepes filled with brown sugar and coconut flakes with a side of coconut sorbet

comment.text: This place isn't near me but I had the delicious beef rendang and will definitely be back!
Great food! Excellent service and perfect ambiance. Our jackfruit dish was just amazing! Perfectly spiced. Don't forget to get their icecream. It was amazing!

photos.caption: NR1. PLANT BASED RENDANG RICE PLATE

comment.text: Perhaps our expectation is too high or we are just not familiar with Indonesian cuisine. We drove from Milton to try Rijsttafel for the first time in our lives. (We spent two weeks in Amsterdam a couple of years ago but never managed to experience Rijsttafel which was a huge regret.) We ordered the small plates of sea tasting, one chicken soup, one mushroom soup, and one Rijsttafel. We each had a cocktail and we had the dessert crepe rolls. The presentation of everything was pretty nice. The restaurant interior decor was good too. The service was attentive, although not anticipatory. The drinks were good but not fantastic. The scallops were pretty good, the roasted fish was VERY tough, the crab tempura was fine but didn't taste too much like crab. The Rijsttafel had a good variety but nothing fancy. The best part of the whole night was definitely the dessert. The crepe rolls are made in house, as is the sorbet. This was delicious. The price is very good but the overall food is mediocre. I guess my biggest complaint is that more than half of the menu is fried food. I didn't think Indonesian had so much fried food but admittedly, I'm not familiar.
We visited this restaurant on a busy Saturday. The food was delicious. If I could give 10 stars I would. I'll def.take pictures on my next visit.

I have eaten at Win over 30 times. I have never had a bad experience. I love the small plates, the steak and lamb sates.  The service is amazing (eat anywhere 30+ times and you become part of the family).  

My wife and I ate at Win on Valentine's Day and the ambiance was wonderful. They gave roses to all the women in the restaurant, and the normal mood lighting was supplemented with candles. 

i love Win.

Win became an instant favorite for me. I like to go during lunch because you can't beat the specials. The tempura Brussels sprouts are so delicious! I could eat them everyday! The lamb saté is also must have for me. I've tried a few other menu items as well that were all good but the lamb saté and Brussels have my heart lol.

My own rijsttafel sama 3 different sambals, what????
The cuisine at WIN spans across Sumatra, Java, Bali and beyond.  A long awaited treat for sure! The people are fantastically gracious and I expected nothing less.  A "WIN" for Atlanta!

Crepe Rolls
Rijsttafel Tasting

Had high expectations for this place but sadly didn't meet them. I always see this place on my drive but also heard good things about it on TikTok so my friend and I decided to try it. 

Service: I booked us a table but when we got there apparently they didn't have anything for me. I even showed host the reservation on my phone but he said oh it's OK I'll seat you anyways. We got seated quickly but the server we had was very slow. I had I ask for water refills several times, to the point where I had to ask other servers because our server was no where to be found. When I came to checks he justjust brought it over and we actually wanted dessert. When we asked he actually discouraged us from getting dessert because it was busy. We said that's ok we would wait but in the end we didn't get it because we felt like he just didn't want us to get any.

Food: tbh food was not good at all. The only thing I enjoyed were the Rica Rica Shrimp Al Ajillo. We also got the Chicken & Egg Pillows which tasted like a samosa to me. For dinner I got the Yellow Chicken Curry Rice Plate which was honestly just confusing to me taste wise. It was like teriyaki chicken with Thai yellow curry. It wasn't spicy either so I had to add some hot sauce to add more flavor. My friend got the fried chicken dish which just tasted like regular fried chicken. 

Overall, I wasn't impressed with the food and the service didn't help. Unfortunately, would not recommend.

The food was absolutely amazing I had the Ribs and my mom had the Duck. The service was pretty good too, I enjoyed our waitress I didn't catch her name though but she was nice. And the place was very clean, pretty and just a very nice place to sit and enjoy quality food. We got plenty of food, 5 appetizers, 2 entrees, 3 drinks and dessert for about $150. Decently priced place as well, high ly recommend!

SG1. BEST RIBS IN TOWN SG4. BALI CRISPY DUCK - HALF DUCK CONFIT ON THE BONE

comment.text:
Win was a pretty great experience for my first time having Indonesian food in atlanta. The restaurant is beautifully decorated and the staff/management was so nice!! 

It wasn't super busy when I went, and we were able to get a nice private booth. I had the rijsttafel which was a great way to try a bit of their whole menu. I can't remember what each thing was, but my favorites were the beef rendang and the fish curry. They definitely packed each plate because I had tons of leftovers to take home!

Although the rijsttafel in Amsterdam was much better, Win is a pretty great and cheap option for Indonesian food in the city.
Enak juga nih. Cobain saja. Puas deh. Bakalan balik. Sate is delicious, nasi top bgt. Kalo mau cari Indonesia food, stop disini.

Came last night for my second time. First try was great maybe because I sat at bar so service was better and it was slower during the day. But last night was horrible. Restaurant lacks consistency of serving fresh food and sincere service. Waitresses rushing my order, and still serving me cold food. I sent back chicken satay bc there was no glaze on it and cold, scallops were cold and rubbery so I sent back and they brought back SAME DISH telling me "the chef said it's the sauce" I've literally been here before the condescending service was insulting. I kept food to keep my cool but left no tip just bartender got one bc the only good thing that night. So if you want 50/50 chance of getting cold rubbery scallops and a rushed meal then take a chance. I recommend Sri Thai instead! Will never be back
Food was fantastic, service was 5 star, it's a romantic and beautiful dining room. Our table was intimate. 10/10 I am in love with this place

Plump chicken breast cubes, basted with 'kecap manis' sweet glaze and spices, grilled to perfection, perfectly paired with a creamy peanut sauce and crispy shallots - very juicy and the sauce. Very clean great atmosphere. Awesome service. Loved the kale , chicken and veggies.

If you're looking to try something new, this is the spot. They have an expansive menu of Indonesian food, and so far everything I have tried was good. I would highly recommend all the small plates of the sea if you're looking for something fresh. As far as entrees, you can't go wrong with any of their signature dishes. The  one dish that stood out to me most was their Chicken Curry Plate. It's a great spot to bring your friends, especially at the beautifully decorated bar, or makes for a great date night spot. Giving this review 3 starts being that the main entrées were just lukewarm in my opinion, but all the appetizers/small plates were piping hot.

This place is a gem. Not only were all the dishes good, but also very affordable. They have themed days with special, I went on a Monday & it was $5 wine Monday- love that! The fried rice was simple & delicious, all the satays were tasty too! My only wish is that the food comes out as ready instead of waiting for it all to be done & come out together. Beautiful restaurant nonetheless with tasty food!

photos.caption: SS6. CRUNCHY CALAMARI Scallops SP7. CHICKEN & EGG PILLOWS SH1. FRIED RICE SB5. LAMB SAT SB2. CHICKEN SAT SB3. BALI STYLE PORK SAT

comment.text:
Been seeing great reviews for this place so I dropped by Monday night for dinner. The place was pretty empty so we were seated and served really quickly. It's looks a bit fancy but is actually a bit more casual than it first seems, so don't worry.

When seated, they provide these shrimp (?) puffs with a mild-spicy dipping sauce. A great free appetizer and they even offered to refill it when we finished it (which we took). We ordered the Small Plate Tasting, which lets you pick three small plates for $20. We got the pork wontons, vegetable spring rolls, and the chicken and egg pillows, per the server's recommendations. All were great, especially the pillows - such a unique flavor and a great dipping sauce (wasn't sure what was in it .. onions and some spice?). We also got lamb sate skewers (comes with 6). It comes with a sweet dipping sauce, kind of like a teriyaki sauce. The skewers are a bit small and a little too burnt, but pretty decent. Usually lamb has a weird aftertaste, which I didn't get from these so that was good.

Overall - I rate WIN very highly. The food was pretty good and decently priced. Part of why I rate this so highly is because there are so many other menu items that I want to come back for (and there's so much variety!) - so this place definitely pulled me in. Our host/server was also super friendly - he checked up on us often, offered shrimp puff refills, and offered some great recommendations. Definitely recommend coming here for a nice and flavorful meal!

**Parking might be rough. The parking lot up front is pretty small. There may be a parking lot in the back, but not sure.

photos.caption: Left to right: Pork wontons, Vegetable Spring Rolls, Chicken and Egg Pillows

comment.text: Finally had a chance to try this place after driving by a few times.  It was quite busy when we came so everything took awhile. I ordered the fried chicken which wasn't bad.  My friend ordered the curry dish which she didn't particularly like.  I would say overall for the food and price point, maybe not the best experience.  We also were interested in dessert, however the waiter seemed overwhelmed and told us it would take awhile and didn't really seem like he wanted to take our order for dessert, so we ended up leaving since it felt we were being rushed to leave.

This place is a great tapa place! We got the Chicken Curry Plate which wasn't my favorite curry the the rest of the plate was amazing, the Lamb Sate Skewers which were sooo tasty and served with a nice jam like sauce would definitely recommend and then we also got the Rijsttafel Tasting which was amazing every single dish was very tasteful and perfect for two people to share! Would definitely return when in the area! 

Our server was Stephanie and she was amazing! Very attentive, knowledgeable and overall helped create a great experience :)
